external_knowledge:
- "Active representatives" are those currently serving in an official capacity;
- "Total representatives" include both active and inactive members;
- "Representatives spread across multiple counties" indicates the geographical reach of a party's influence.

- "dawn of the new decade" refers to the year 2020;
- "roots spreading through the soil" is a metaphor for representatives who are associated with multiple counties;
- "members of parliament" refers to representatives.

- "Seasoned representatives" refers to representatives who have been in office for more than 10 years;
- "Standing tall for over a decade" means they have served for more than 10 years;
- "Pillar of experience" refers to a representative who has been in office for more than 10 years;
- "More than one such pillar of experience" means the party has at least two representatives who have been in office for more than 10 years.

- Active representatives are those whose status is 'active';
- The year they took office is stored in the `since` column;
- The number of counties they represent is determined by the count of `county_id` entries in the `representative_counties` table.

- 'seasoned representatives' refers to representatives born in the 1900s;
- 'weaving their influence' refers to representing districts;
- 'new age' refers to the 2020s.

- "Long-serving representatives" are those who have been in office for more than 5 years;
- "Currently representing" means they have not yet ended their representation (i.e., `representation_end_date` is `NULL`);
- "Multiple counties" refers to representing at least 2 counties.

- "Leaders who stand out" refers to representatives ranked first in the most populous district;
- "Most populous regions" refers to districts with the highest population;
- "Spanning multiple territories" refers to representatives associated with more than one county;
- "Political group" refers to the party the representative belongs to.

- 'Multiple counties' refers to more than one county;
- 'Significant populations' refers to counties with a total population greater than 100,000;
- 'System access frequency' is the number of times a representative accessed the system with the 'view' access type.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(representative_id) AS republican_members_count
FROM representatives
WHERE party_id = (SELECT party_id FROM parties WHERE party_name = 'Republican');
